        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The cursor reset sequence change seems fine, though I can't easily test those terminals to see how they handle that sequence.\r\n\r\nI can't speak to the updates in `message.c`. I guess that's what's supposed to fix the linked issues, but I don't see how, nor do I know enough to say. It seems like it would affect Linux and Windows if there were a bug there, but I definitely don't have the screen clearing problem on Linux described in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25619. I would have thought it would be something in e.g. `terminfo_disable` or `terminfo_stop`.",
